WEBVTT

00:02.794 --> 00:05.588
<i>♪ The Simpsons ♪</i>

00:08.842 --> 00:10.885
(bell ringing)

00:12.762 --> 00:14.639
(whistle blowing)

00:19.019 --> 00:20.812
(beeping)

00:28.069 --> 00:32.449
(jazzy solo)

00:32.532 --> 00:34.451
(tires screeching)

00:35.994 --> 00:37.078
D'oh!

00:37.162 --> 00:39.372
-Aah!
-(tires screech)

00:57.307 --> 01:01.186
-I need one 29-cent stamp.
-That's $1.85.

01:01.269 --> 01:03.980
-I want $2.00 worth of gas, please.
-$4.20.

01:04.064 --> 01:06.024
-(bell dings)
-How much is your penny candy?

01:06.107 --> 01:09.444
-Surprisingly expensive.
-MARTIN: What a rip-off!

01:09.527 --> 01:12.030
-(door chimes)
-This is what I think of your store!

01:12.113 --> 01:14.157
-(grunting)
-(door chimes)

01:14.240 --> 01:16.576
Silly customer!

01:16.659 --> 01:19.245
You cannot hurt a twinkie!

01:20.371 --> 01:24.250
(sniffing)

01:24.334 --> 01:27.670
Jiminy Cricket!
Whoo! Expired ham.

01:32.050 --> 01:35.220
Well, this time I've gone too
far. No. No one will fall for--

01:35.303 --> 01:37.222
Woo-hoo! Cheap meat!

01:37.305 --> 01:40.308
Ooh, this one's open.
(gobbling)

01:45.230 --> 01:49.025
-Ooh! Stomach churning!
-(stomach grumbles)

01:49.109 --> 01:51.194
Bowels clenching.

01:51.277 --> 01:53.613
-Not much time.
-(thuds)

01:53.696 --> 01:56.741
Must finish.
(gobbles)

01:56.825 --> 01:59.119
(alarm blaring)

01:59.202 --> 02:03.373
Well, sir, Homer's illness was either
caused by ingesting spoiled food

02:03.456 --> 02:07.043
or some sort of voodoo curse.

02:07.127 --> 02:09.420
Hey, we've just been
working the eyes.

02:11.714 --> 02:14.259
-(door chimes)
-Your old meat made me sick!

02:14.342 --> 02:17.846
Oh, I'm so sorry. Please accept
five pounds of frozen shrimp.

02:17.929 --> 02:22.433
(sniffing) This shrimp isn't frozen,
and it smells funny.

02:22.517 --> 02:24.477
-Okay. Ten pounds.
-Whoo-hoo!

02:24.561 --> 02:26.855
(alarm blaring)

02:26.938 --> 02:28.857
<i>(barking)</i>

02:33.903 --> 02:36.948
-MAN: <i>Brought to you by--</i>
<i>-(barking continues)</i>

02:40.368 --> 02:43.121
That dog can sell anything.

02:43.204 --> 02:44.831
<i>Good evening.</i>
<i>Here's an update on last week's</i>

02:44.914 --> 02:47.250
<i>nursing-home exposé,</i>
<i>"Geezers in Freezers."</i>

02:47.333 --> 02:50.253
<i>It turns out the rest home</i>
<i>was adequately heated.</i>

02:50.336 --> 02:53.631
<i>The footage you saw was</i>
<i>of a fur-storage facility.</i>

02:53.715 --> 02:57.802
<i>We've also been told to apologize</i>
<i>for using the term "geezers."</i>

02:57.886 --> 03:01.848
<i>Now, coming up next, "The case</i>
<i>of the cantankerous old geezer."</i>

03:01.931 --> 03:03.933
-Ohh! Urp!
-(stomach grumbles)

03:04.017 --> 03:07.437
Rancid meat attack!
Stupid parasites!

03:07.520 --> 03:09.898
Is there no way
I can find justice?

03:09.981 --> 03:13.234
<i>If you have a consumer</i>
<i>complaint, just call this number.</i>

03:13.318 --> 03:14.319
Boring.

03:14.402 --> 03:16.404
Dad, you should blow
the whistle on the Kwik-E-Mart.

03:16.487 --> 03:19.324
BROCKMAN: <i>And now a message from</i>
<i>the Church of Latter-Day Saints.</i>

03:19.407 --> 03:21.159
<i>(dog barking)</i>

03:21.242 --> 03:25.038
-Dad, are you listening to me?
-Shh! Lisa! The dog is barking.

03:28.166 --> 03:30.752
All right. Are you willing to go
undercover to nail this creep?

03:30.835 --> 03:35.340
No way, man! No way, man!
Get yourself another patsy, man!

03:35.423 --> 03:37.717
No way am I wearin'
a freakin' wire.

03:37.800 --> 03:39.761
All right, all right, all right.
Would you be willing to wear

03:39.844 --> 03:42.430
-a hidden camera and microphone?
-Oh, that I'll wear.

03:44.432 --> 03:46.559
We've come up
with a camera so tiny

03:46.643 --> 03:48.102
it fits into this
oversized novelty hat.

03:48.186 --> 03:50.355
(groaning)

03:50.438 --> 03:52.732
Now go get us some
incriminating footage.

03:52.815 --> 03:55.443
And remember, you have to get in
and out in 10 minutes,

03:55.526 --> 03:58.696
-or you'll suffer permanent neck damage.
-He's not kiddin'.

03:59.822 --> 04:02.283
(groaning)

04:02.367 --> 04:05.495
(footsteps clattering)

04:05.578 --> 04:07.455
(door chimes)

04:11.751 --> 04:15.004
-Huh?
-Don't be alarmed, Apu.

04:15.088 --> 04:18.841
Just go about your daily routine
like I'm not wearing the hat.

04:18.925 --> 04:22.387
Your headgear seems to be
emitting a buzzing noise, sir.

04:22.470 --> 04:24.389
Perhaps you have
a bee in your bonnet.

04:24.472 --> 04:28.434
Bee?
(screaming)

04:28.518 --> 04:31.521
(panting)

04:31.604 --> 04:35.191
Homer, that hat's been
with the station for 20 years.

04:35.275 --> 04:37.610
He had one day left
till retirement.

04:37.694 --> 04:39.070
<i>♪ La la la la la ♪</i>

04:39.153 --> 04:41.614
<i>Well, time to</i>
<i>replenish the hot-dog roller.</i>

04:41.698 --> 04:43.574
<i>♪ La la ♪</i>
<i>Oops!</i>

04:46.411 --> 04:49.580
<i>Oh, no.</i>
<i>It is encrusted with filth.</i>

04:49.664 --> 04:52.417
<i>Oh, well.</i>
<i>Let's sell it anyway.</i>

04:52.500 --> 04:57.922
<i>Now, this is just between me</i>
<i>and you, smashed hat. (chuckling)</i>

04:58.006 --> 05:00.550
Hot diggety dog!
We've got him, Mr. Simpson.

05:00.633 --> 05:03.303
Now, let's-- Mr. Simpson?

05:03.386 --> 05:05.847
<i>One hot dog, please.</i>

05:05.930 --> 05:08.933
<i>(dog barking on TV)</i>

05:09.017 --> 05:11.519
<i>Apu, will you ever stop</i>
<i>selling spoiled meat?</i>

05:11.602 --> 05:15.023
<i>No. I mean, yes.</i>
<i>I mean-- Uh-oh.</i>

05:15.106 --> 05:19.277
-I think I come off very well.
-Monster! Run, children!

05:19.360 --> 05:21.112
(panicked shouting)

05:21.195 --> 05:23.239
Apu Nahasapeemapetilon,

05:23.323 --> 05:25.575
you have disgraced
the Kwik-E-Mart corporation.

05:25.658 --> 05:28.036
But, sir, I was only following
standard procedure.

05:28.119 --> 05:30.413
Ah, true. But it's also
standard procedure

05:30.496 --> 05:33.875
to blame any problems
on a scapegoat or sacrificial lamb.

05:33.958 --> 05:36.544
Uh-huh. And if I can
obtain for you these animals?

05:36.627 --> 05:38.963
I'm sorry, Apu.
I have no choice.

05:39.047 --> 05:42.091
-You can no longer wear this name patch.
-(gasps)

05:42.175 --> 05:45.845
And you can no longer tell
people about our fried pickles.

05:45.928 --> 05:49.432
Now, turn in
your pricing gun.

05:49.515 --> 05:51.392
Oh!

05:53.269 --> 05:55.938
The other one too.

06:00.318 --> 06:05.531
Oh! Fired after all these years
of loyal service.

06:05.615 --> 06:08.493
-I don't want to live anymore! Oh!
-Give me that wiener!

06:08.576 --> 06:11.037
-No! I don't want to live, sir!
-Give me that wiener!

06:11.120 --> 06:13.247
-(grunting)
-No, Apu! It's not worth it!

06:13.331 --> 06:15.750
What do I do now?

06:15.833 --> 06:20.505
I've been drummed out of my profession.
I'm a disgrace.

06:20.588 --> 06:25.009
Even this babbling brook sounds
almost like mocking laughter.

06:25.093 --> 06:27.804
(laughter)

06:27.887 --> 06:30.390
Who needs money
when we got feathers?

06:34.602 --> 06:37.647
(chittering)

06:37.730 --> 06:38.981
Hmm.

06:42.735 --> 06:45.113
(thunderclap)

06:45.196 --> 06:48.533
This is all because
of Homer Simpson.

06:48.616 --> 06:51.702
-(laughing)
<i>-(laughter on TV)</i>

06:51.786 --> 06:53.788
Oh, oh, stop!

06:53.871 --> 06:56.874
<i>Yo, check this out.</i>
<i>Black guys drive a car like this.</i>

06:56.958 --> 06:59.544
<i>-♪♪ (scatting)</i>
<i>-(audience laughing)</i>

06:59.627 --> 07:03.881
<i>Yeah, but white guys, see, they drive</i>
<i>a car like this. ♪♪ (scatting)</i>

07:03.965 --> 07:09.470
<i>-(laughter, applause)</i>
-It's true! It's true! We're so lame.

07:09.554 --> 07:12.223
It is time to settle the score.

07:15.643 --> 07:17.478
Huh?

07:17.562 --> 07:20.481
(thunderclaps continue)

07:20.565 --> 07:23.234
Aah!

07:23.317 --> 07:25.278
(screaming)

07:27.530 --> 07:29.949
(screaming)

07:30.032 --> 07:33.578
No! Don't kill me! I didn't know
there was film in that camera in that hat!

07:33.661 --> 07:36.706
I was unaware!
I was unaware!

07:36.789 --> 07:39.375
Mr. Simpson,
you misunderstand me.

07:39.459 --> 07:42.670
In my village, this is
the traditional pose of apology.

07:42.753 --> 07:45.756
-Oh.
-You know, now that I think about it,

07:45.840 --> 07:47.425
it may be a little confusing.

07:47.508 --> 07:49.385
Many have died needlessly.

07:49.469 --> 07:53.222
I have come to make amends, sir.
At first, I blamed you for squealing.

07:53.306 --> 07:56.267
But then I realized
it was I who wronged you.

07:56.350 --> 08:00.021
So I have come to work
off my debt. I am at your service.

08:00.104 --> 08:01.772
You're selling what now?

08:01.856 --> 08:06.027
I'm selling only the concept
of karmic realignment.

08:06.110 --> 08:07.487
You can't sell that!

08:07.570 --> 08:09.363
Karma can only be
portioned out by the cosmos.

08:09.447 --> 08:13.493
-He's got me there.
-(metal scraping)

08:13.576 --> 08:17.538
-HOMER: Is he still out there?
-Yes. He's raking leaves.

08:17.622 --> 08:19.624
What? That's your job!

08:19.707 --> 08:21.918
If he starts doing
Lisa's wood chopping--

08:22.001 --> 08:24.754
If he wants to make it up to you
so badly, I think you should let him.

08:24.837 --> 08:29.091
Okay, okay. I'll let him.
But then I get a Chipwich. Okay?

08:29.175 --> 08:32.595
It is an honor to begin
repaying my debt to you.

08:32.678 --> 08:35.598
Back in Rahmatpur,
I was considered quite the gourmet.

08:35.681 --> 08:39.560
Hmm. It certainly is exotic.

08:39.644 --> 08:42.188
-(panting)
-Oh, Lisa, is that too spicy for you?

08:42.271 --> 08:44.273
I can see through time.

08:44.357 --> 08:46.609
(gulping)
Stop being such babies.

08:46.692 --> 08:48.945
You can't be afraid
to try new things.

08:49.028 --> 08:52.865
For instance, tonight I'm using a--
Apu, what do you call this thing again?

08:52.949 --> 08:56.953
-A napkin.
-(chuckling) Outrageous!

08:58.996 --> 09:00.957
All right. Why do you want
to become a part

09:01.040 --> 09:02.500
of the Kwik-E-Mart family?

09:02.583 --> 09:04.210
Because I like people,

09:04.293 --> 09:06.212
and I need a place
where I'll be out of the sun.

09:06.295 --> 09:08.464
-Thank you.
-(belches)

09:08.548 --> 09:10.800
Hmm. He's head and shoulders
above everyone else.

09:10.883 --> 09:13.886
-Wait. There's one more applicant.
-Name?

09:13.970 --> 09:16.556
-James Woods.
-Previous job experience?

09:16.639 --> 09:22.061
Ooh, uh, gee, <i>True Believer, </i>uh, <i>Salvador,</i>
<i>Onion Field, The Hard Way.</i>

09:22.144 --> 09:24.522
Wait-wait a minute!
Those aren't convenience stores.

09:24.605 --> 09:25.982
that sounds like the resume
of a Hollywood movie star.

09:26.482 --> 09:27.483
Uh, yeah, well-- Hmm.

09:27.567 --> 09:30.069
(both gasp)
James woods!

09:30.152 --> 09:32.405
Why would you want
to work at a Kwik-E-Mart?

09:32.488 --> 09:35.825
(chuckles) Well, uh, to be honest,
in my upcoming movie...

09:35.908 --> 09:38.536
I'm gonna be playing this tightly wound
convenience-store clerk,

09:38.619 --> 09:42.164
and, you know, I kinda like to research
my roles and really get into it.

09:42.248 --> 09:45.751
For instance, <i>True Believer. </i>I actually
worked in a law firm for two months.

09:45.835 --> 09:48.170
And in the film <i>Chaplin--</i>
I had a little cameo in that--

09:48.254 --> 09:51.882
I actually traveled in time
back to the '20s where--

09:51.966 --> 09:55.344
-Well, (chuckles) I've said too much.
-Welcome aboard.

09:55.428 --> 09:58.889
♪♪ (humming)

09:58.973 --> 10:01.309
Hm? Hm? Hm? Hm?

10:01.392 --> 10:03.269
-Good morning, sir.
-(screams)

10:03.352 --> 10:07.398
Relax, please. You do not have anything
I have not seen before.

10:07.481 --> 10:11.986
-What the--
-Uh, I like to keep a lollipop there.

10:13.863 --> 10:16.824
<i>-♪ La la la la ♪</i>
-(groans)

10:16.907 --> 10:19.535
Apu, we usually store
our cans in the cupboard.

10:19.619 --> 10:21.370
Well, they'll never move
that way.

10:21.454 --> 10:23.873
Mmm! Corn!
Haven't had that in a while.

10:23.956 --> 10:26.417
Yeah! Delicious corn.

10:26.500 --> 10:29.003
-TOGETHER: Bye.
-Hm.

10:29.086 --> 10:33.007
Oh, we're low on milk for Maggie.
You wanna come with me to the Kwik-E-Mart?

10:33.090 --> 10:35.176
Please, Mrs. Simpson.

10:35.259 --> 10:39.764
I-- I cannot go there. That is
the scene of my spiritual depantsing.

10:39.847 --> 10:43.976
Umm, well, I guess we could go
to that new Monstromart.

10:46.729 --> 10:48.856
♪♪ (Muzak)

10:53.069 --> 10:56.989
Ooh! That's a good price
for 12 pounds of nutmeg.

10:57.073 --> 11:01.452
Ooh! Great selection and
rock-bottom prices. But where is the love?

11:01.535 --> 11:03.579
MAN (on P.A.):
<i>Attention Monstromart shoppers.</i>

11:03.663 --> 11:06.248
<i>Just a reminder that we love</i>
<i>each and every one of you.</i>

11:06.332 --> 11:09.502
-(shoppers) Aww!
-Hm!

11:11.629 --> 11:15.424
Excuse me, ma'am.
Where are the lampshades?

11:15.508 --> 11:18.552
-Ma'am?
-(liquid pouring)

11:18.636 --> 11:21.347
Oh! I've killed her!

11:21.430 --> 11:23.557
It's all happening again!

11:23.641 --> 11:27.603
-(sobbing, screaming)
-Mm-hmm.

11:29.563 --> 11:32.983
(both gasp, scream)

11:33.067 --> 11:35.069
Help me! Help me!

11:35.152 --> 11:38.447
(gurgling)
Mmm! It's cran-tastic!

11:41.033 --> 11:45.579
Uh, Mrs. Simpson, the express line
is the fastest line not always.

11:45.663 --> 11:49.125
That old man up front,
he is starved for attention.

11:49.208 --> 11:51.085
He will talk
the cashier's head off.

11:51.168 --> 11:55.381
Ah, there's an interesting story
behind this nickel.

11:55.464 --> 11:58.759
In 1957, I remember it was.

11:58.843 --> 12:03.556
I got up in the morning and
made myself a piece of toast.

12:03.639 --> 12:08.352
I set the toaster to three--
medium brown.

12:08.436 --> 12:11.355
-Let's go to... that line.
-But that's the longest.

12:11.439 --> 12:16.068
Yes, but look-- all pathetic single men.
Only cash, no chitchat.

12:16.152 --> 12:18.529
(rapid cash-register sounds)

12:20.030 --> 12:22.616
Mmm!

12:22.700 --> 12:25.786
Seventy-five, 85, 90
and a dollar.

12:25.870 --> 12:27.788
Thank you and come again.
Hey, wait a minute! Hey!

12:27.872 --> 12:31.751
Uh, eh, could I just
ask you a question?

12:31.834 --> 12:36.464
Did you-- huh! Did you believe that?
I mean, the way I gave you the change?

12:36.547 --> 12:41.135
Did I sound like a real Kwik-E-Mart,
you know, kinda guy?

12:41.218 --> 12:44.180
Actually, I thought
it was a little labored.

12:44.263 --> 12:47.183
You gotta lose yourself
in the moment, man.

12:47.266 --> 12:50.644
Yeah. Like-- Yeah! Great. Okay. Let-let's
just try that again. Okay? Come on.

12:50.728 --> 12:54.607
Hey. Come on. Hey-ey-ey! Hey, get over
here! Okay. Now, you're you, I'm me.

12:54.690 --> 12:59.320
-I'm me?
-Hey, don't jerk me around, fella.

12:59.403 --> 13:01.739
(all gobbling, gulping)

13:01.822 --> 13:05.117
-Pass the chutney.
-Apu, you've been so helpful.

13:05.201 --> 13:08.496
If it weren't for him, we'd
still be in line at the Monstromart.

13:08.579 --> 13:12.708
-And he taught me how to play the shehnai.
-♪♪ (shrill notes)

13:12.792 --> 13:15.878
(shudders) That's even worse than
the album Grampa released.

13:15.961 --> 13:19.006
And he taught me how to do this.
(grunting)

13:19.089 --> 13:22.426
I got out of school, 'cause I told 'em
I was mangled in a car wreck.

13:22.510 --> 13:26.055
-Thank you all for the kind praise.
-Well, you deserve it.

13:26.138 --> 13:30.643
All these vegetables are really clearing
the cholesterol out of the old heart.

13:30.726 --> 13:33.062
(beating)

13:33.145 --> 13:35.189
(electrical crackling)

13:35.272 --> 13:39.443
(slowly)
Ahh. Apu friend me good.

13:39.527 --> 13:43.364
I think what my father's saying is
you're like a member of the family now.

13:43.447 --> 13:47.993
I feel that way too. You see,
whether igloo, hut or lean-to...

13:48.077 --> 13:50.329
or a geodesic dome,

13:50.412 --> 13:54.667
there's no structure I have been
to which I'd rather call my home.

13:54.750 --> 13:56.752
Hello. Aah!

13:56.836 --> 13:59.296
<i>♪ When I first arrived</i>
<i>you were all such jerks ♪</i>

13:59.380 --> 14:02.800
<i>♪ But now I've come</i>
<i>to love your quirks ♪</i>

14:02.883 --> 14:04.718
<i>♪ Maggie with</i>
<i>her eyes so bright ♪</i>

14:04.802 --> 14:07.096
<i>♪ Marge with hair</i>
<i>by Frank Lloyd Wright ♪</i>

14:07.179 --> 14:09.473
<i>♪ Lisa can philosophize ♪</i>

14:09.557 --> 14:11.475
<i>♪ Bart's adept</i>
<i>at spinning lies ♪</i>

14:11.559 --> 14:13.686
<i>♪ Homer's a delightful fella ♪</i>

14:13.769 --> 14:17.314
<i>-♪ Sorry 'bout the salmonella ♪</i>
-Heh-heh! That's okay.

14:17.398 --> 14:20.150
-Aah!
<i>-♪ Who needs the Kwik-E-Mart ♪</i>

14:20.234 --> 14:22.653
<i>♪ Now here's</i>
<i>the tricky part ♪</i>

14:22.736 --> 14:26.740
<i>♪ Oh, won't you</i>
<i>rhyme with me ♪</i>

14:26.824 --> 14:28.826
<i>♪ Who needs</i>
<i>the Kwik-E-Mart ♪</i>

14:28.909 --> 14:30.911
<i>♪ Their floors</i>
<i>are sticky-mart ♪</i>

14:30.995 --> 14:33.080
<i>♪ They made Dad sicky-mart ♪</i>

14:33.163 --> 14:35.499
<i>♪ Let's hurl a bricky-mart ♪</i>

14:35.583 --> 14:37.501
<i>♪ The Kwik-E-Mart is real-- ♪</i>
D'oh!

14:39.461 --> 14:42.923
ALL:
<i>♪ Who needs the Kwik-E-Mart ♪</i>

14:43.007 --> 14:46.176
<i>-♪ Not me ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Forget the Kwik-E-Mart ♪</i>

14:46.260 --> 14:48.387
<i>♪ Good-bye to Kwik-E-Mart ♪</i>

14:48.470 --> 14:51.098
<i>♪ Who needs the Kwik-E-Mart ♪</i>

14:51.181 --> 14:52.725
<i>♪ Not me ♪</i>

14:56.812 --> 15:01.859
Ahh. Everything really wrapped up nicely.
Hmm. Much quicker than usual.

15:01.942 --> 15:05.029
I guess we've learned that happiness
is wherever you find it.

15:05.112 --> 15:09.909
And we've all found happiness,
every one of us.

15:09.992 --> 15:12.161
-(Apu crying)
-(TV clicks on)

15:15.080 --> 15:16.040
Hey, what's that sound?

15:16.123 --> 15:19.251
(crying continues)

15:19.335 --> 15:23.756
<i>♪ Who needs</i>
<i>the Kwik-E-Mart ♪</i>

15:23.839 --> 15:28.761
<i>♪ I do ♪</i>

15:28.844 --> 15:33.432
Hey, he's not happy at all!
He lied to us through song!

15:33.515 --> 15:35.476
I hate when people do that!

15:39.229 --> 15:43.317
I can't lie to myself, you know.
I do miss my Kwik-E-Mart.

15:43.400 --> 15:45.945
Isn't there anything you can do to
get your job back?

15:46.028 --> 15:49.406
I must go to the head office
and appeal my case.

15:49.490 --> 15:51.075
I'm coming with you!

15:51.158 --> 15:54.328
I got you fired.
It's the least I can do.

15:54.411 --> 15:56.372
Well, the least I can do is
absolutely nothing.

15:56.455 --> 15:59.708
But I'll go you one better
and come along.

15:59.792 --> 16:02.211
-But, sir, the head office is in India.
-Okay.

16:02.294 --> 16:06.298
-Dad, that's over 10,000 miles away.
-I'm aware of that!

16:06.382 --> 16:08.884
-That's over 16,000 kilometers.
-D'oh!

16:20.312 --> 16:24.566
I'm sorry we couldn't take a cab, but I
spent my last dollar on the plane tickets.

16:24.650 --> 16:26.443
-HOMER: Are we in India yet?
-APU: No.

16:26.527 --> 16:28.153
-Are we in India yet?
-No.

16:28.237 --> 16:29.363
-Are we in India yet?
-No.

16:29.446 --> 16:31.198
-Are we in India yet?
-No.

16:31.281 --> 16:33.867
Oh, wait... now we are.

16:35.995 --> 16:38.247
T-Tony, T-Tony,
y-you're my agent.

16:38.330 --> 16:40.499
You have to do something
about this.

16:40.582 --> 16:43.252
Uh! How can it be the same movie
if they've changed my character

16:43.335 --> 16:47.673
from a tightly wound convenience-store
clerk to a jittery Eskimo firefighter?

16:47.756 --> 16:51.385
Uh-huh. Uh-huh. Mm-hmm.

16:51.468 --> 16:54.805
Well, actually, that's--
that's a pretty good explanation.

16:54.888 --> 16:57.558
Now this is gross-- this'll be gross
points, right, on this new-- okay.

16:57.641 --> 17:00.519
Yeah, 'cause those monkey-- yeah. Okay.
Great. Okay. Look. Book me a flight,

17:00.602 --> 17:02.980
rent me an igloo, and tell those dorks
at the Kwik-E-Mart

17:03.063 --> 17:04.398
that, boom, I am out of here.

17:04.481 --> 17:08.318
I'm a dot. I'm gone. Okay? What do you
mean, I gotta give two weeks notice?

17:08.402 --> 17:11.989
Why, you damn, frickin', no good
mother-- (beeping) cheese!

17:12.072 --> 17:13.824
No, not you.
I'm just talkin' to my oven.

17:17.369 --> 17:20.205
<i>♪ If you're saved and you know it</i>
<i>clap your hands ♪</i>

17:20.289 --> 17:22.583
<i>♪ If you're saved and you know it</i>
<i>clap your hands ♪</i>

17:22.666 --> 17:25.753
-♪♪ (continues, indistinct)
-Oh, great. Christians.

17:25.836 --> 17:29.923
MAN: <i>Attention, passengers. Dinner</i>
<i>is now being served in the dining car.</i>

17:30.007 --> 17:32.801
(all clamoring)

17:40.851 --> 17:42.936
(both panting, grunting)

17:43.020 --> 17:44.605
-Ooh-ooh!
-There she is.

17:44.688 --> 17:49.401
There she is, the world's first
convenience store.

17:52.112 --> 17:55.532
-This isn't very convenient.
-Must you dump on everything we do?

17:55.616 --> 17:56.992
(bell chimes)

17:58.619 --> 17:59.620
(bell chimes)

18:01.080 --> 18:03.415
♪♪ (Indian Muzak)

18:03.499 --> 18:07.419
He is the benevolent,
enlightened president and C.E.O.

18:07.503 --> 18:10.214
of Kwik-E-Mart,
and in Ohio, Stop-O-Mart.

18:10.297 --> 18:13.342
-(slurping)
-He is the one I must ask for my job back.

18:13.425 --> 18:15.469
Approach, my sons.

18:16.678 --> 18:19.139
(slurping continues)

18:19.223 --> 18:22.226
You may ask me
three questions.

18:22.309 --> 18:24.686
That's great,
because all I need is one.

18:24.770 --> 18:27.397
-Are you really the head of Kwik-E-Mart?
-Yes.

18:27.481 --> 18:28.649
-Really?
-Yes.

18:28.732 --> 18:30.275
-You?
-Yes.

18:30.359 --> 18:33.320
I hope this has been
enlightening for you.

18:33.403 --> 18:35.572
-But I must--
-Thank you. Come again.

18:35.656 --> 18:37.658
-But--
-Thank you. Come again.

18:37.741 --> 18:40.702
Well, that was a big bust.

18:40.786 --> 18:42.830
Is he really the head
of the Kwik-E-Mart?

18:42.913 --> 18:45.165
-(angry groan)
-No need to apologize, Apu.

18:45.249 --> 18:48.460
It was as much my fault
as it was yours.

18:48.544 --> 18:50.420
-(growling)
-(gagging)

18:50.504 --> 18:54.424
Okay, Apu!
I accept your apology.

18:54.508 --> 18:56.385
(both screaming)

18:57.761 --> 18:58.929
TOGETHER:
Dad! Dad!

18:59.012 --> 19:00.430
What'd you bring us?
What'd you bring?

19:00.514 --> 19:03.517
-How did it go?
-Fine! Oh, I mean, not good.

19:03.600 --> 19:08.147
I'm sorry, Apu. But remember--
<i>♪ Who needs the Kwik-E-Mart ♪</i>

19:08.230 --> 19:10.524
Do you mind?
I'm not in the mood.

19:10.607 --> 19:13.485
Apu, if it'll make you
feel any better,

19:13.569 --> 19:16.530
I've learned that life is one
crushing defeat after another...

19:16.613 --> 19:19.533
until you just wish
Flanders was dead.

19:19.616 --> 19:23.287
Yes, yes. You are right, sir.
I've got to accept my fate.

19:23.370 --> 19:25.747
I have feared it
for long enough now.

19:25.831 --> 19:29.626
I'm going to go down to the Kwik-E-Mart,
and I am going to face my demon!

19:29.710 --> 19:32.754
Oh, that'll work out great!
We're out of Lucky Charms.

19:39.469 --> 19:43.056
-(door chimes)
-(delighted gasp)

19:43.140 --> 19:46.602
Ah, my old Squishee machine.

19:48.937 --> 19:51.273
And my scum bucket with flies.

19:53.650 --> 19:56.028
And the hot-check list.

19:56.111 --> 19:59.948
Hey, hey, you're Apu Nahasapeemapetilon,
aren't ya? I mean, you're the--

20:00.032 --> 20:03.202
God, you're-- you're like the guy!
You're a legend around here.

20:03.285 --> 20:07.080
Can I ask you-- is it true you once
worked 96 hours straight?

20:07.164 --> 20:10.125
Oh, yes.
It was horrible, I tell you.

20:10.209 --> 20:12.836
By the end, I thought I was
a hummingbird of some kind.

20:12.920 --> 20:15.505
Oh, yeah! You know, I studied
your old security tapes.

20:15.589 --> 20:19.218
<i>Fee-ee-ee-ee.</i>

20:20.677 --> 20:22.679
<i>Fee-ee-ee-ee.</i>

20:22.763 --> 20:24.348
In a few minutes,

20:24.431 --> 20:26.725
I try to drink nectar
out of Sanjay's head.

20:26.808 --> 20:30.103
All right, you! Hand over the cash,
and don't try any funny stuff!

20:30.187 --> 20:34.983
Hey, pal. I assure you. If I tried any
funny stuff, you would be in hysterics.

20:35.067 --> 20:38.153
-Hey, you're James Woods!
-Oh, thank you. Yes, yes. Thank you.

20:38.237 --> 20:41.448
Well, Mr. Woods,
your new song is gonna be

20:41.531 --> 20:43.909
-number three with a bullet.
-(gun cocks)

20:43.992 --> 20:45.494
-Uh, I'm not a singer.
-Shut up!

20:47.537 --> 20:50.707
-(frightened gasp)
-No!

20:53.210 --> 20:55.295
-Apu!
-Oh!

20:55.379 --> 20:58.048
The searing kiss of hot lead.

20:58.131 --> 21:02.219
How I've missed you.
I mean, I think I'm dying.

21:02.302 --> 21:04.513
-Uhh.
-Oy.

21:05.555 --> 21:07.474
(Dr. Hibbert chuckling)

21:07.557 --> 21:10.060
Well, you are
a very lucky man, Apu.

21:10.143 --> 21:12.896
You see, the bullet ricocheted
off another bullet

21:12.980 --> 21:16.275
that was lodged in your chest
from a previous robbery.

21:16.358 --> 21:19.069
Apu, you saved my life.

21:19.152 --> 21:21.530
And as a small token of
my appreciation,

21:21.613 --> 21:25.033
I got you your job back
at the Kwik-E-Mart.

21:25.117 --> 21:27.327
Oh! Oh, Mr. Woods, you're--

21:27.411 --> 21:31.540
but as for me, I'm off to battle aliens
on a faraway planet.

21:31.623 --> 21:36.837
-That sounds like a good movie.
-Yes. Yes, a movie. Yes.

21:39.214 --> 21:42.217
Hey, let's all hug Apu.

21:42.301 --> 21:45.053
-SIMPSONS: Aww.
-Ooh!

21:48.849 --> 21:52.269
Hey, there's still time.
Let's hug him again.

21:52.352 --> 21:55.439
-Aww.
-Mm!

22:01.361 --> 22:03.739
♪♪

22:47.032 --> 22:48.116
Shh!

22:51.453 --> 22:54.623
CAPTIONS ENHANCED BY
ROUNDABOUT ENTERTAINMENT INC.
